{"content":"---\ntitle: \"Too many files\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"vbrID67\"\nms.assetid: 2ff203e2-bba6-43ae-b72f-8e92a881c98f\n---\n# Too many files\nEither more files have been created in the root directory than the operating system permits, or more files have been opened than the number specified in the **files=** setting in your CONFIG.SYS file.  \n  \n## To correct this error  \n  \n1.  If your program is opening, closing, or saving files in the root directory, change your program so that it uses a subdirectory.  \n  \n2.  Increase the number of files specified in your **files=** setting in your CONFIG.SYS file, and restart your computer.  \n  \n## See also\n\n- [Error Types](../../../visual-basic/programming-guide/language-features/error-types.md)\n","nodes":[{"pos":[4,124],"embed":true,"restype":"x-metadata","content":"title: \"Too many files\"\nms.date: 07/20/2015\nf1_keywords: \n  - \"vbrID67\"\nms.assetid: 2ff203e2-bba6-43ae-b72f-8e92a881c98f","nodes":[{"content":"Too many files","nodes":[{"pos":[0,14],"content":"Too many files","nodes":[{"content":"Too many files","pos":[0,14]}]}],"path":["title"],"nosxs":false}],"yml":true},{"pos":[131,145],"content":"Too many files","linkify":"Too many files","nodes":[{"content":"Too many files","pos":[0,14]}]},{"pos":[146,346],"content":"Either more files have been created in the root directory than the operating system permits, or more files have been opened than the number specified in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>files=<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> setting in your CONFIG.SYS file.","source":"Either more files have been created in the root directory than the operating system permits, or more files have been opened than the number specified in the **files=** setting in your CONFIG.SYS file."},{"pos":[355,376],"content":"To correct this error","linkify":"To correct this error","nodes":[{"content":"To correct this error","pos":[0,21]}]},{"content":"If your program is opening, closing, or saving files in the r